0111150.text: HydroSonix uses advanced acoustic techniques to disrupt the life cycle of Quagga and Zebra  mussels at various stages. Our device emits a range of sound frequencies that are proven to be effective in deterring these mussels, from their larval stage right through to adulthood.

0111350.text: Say goodbye to harmful chemicals and labor-intensive mechanical removal. AquaSonix offers an eco-friendly solution that targets Quagga mussels without disrupting the surrounding ecosystem.

0111550.text: Our sonic device is easy to install and requires minimal maintenance, making it a practical choice for various facilities including water treatment plants, power stations, marinas, and more.

011330.text: The effectiveness of acoustic techniques lies in their ability to target Quagga mussels at various stages of their life cycle. For instance, ultrasonic frequencies  can cause physical damage to the larvae, preventing them from maturing into adults. At the settlement stage, low and middle frequency vibrations can deter mussels from attaching onto surfaces. For adult mussels, low frequency sound waves can potentially reduce their reproduction and activity.
